.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-CONNTRACK 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-conntrack \- conntrack helper and state assignment for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I conntrack
file assigns conntrack helpers or overrides connection tracking state for
specific traffic flows.  Rows emit rules in the
.B prerouting
chain that call
.B ct helper set
or
.B ct state set
on matching packets.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/conntrack
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ACTION	yes	helper name (e.g. ftp, tftp, sip) or CT target keyword
SOURCE	yes	Source address or zone:address (or - for any)
DEST	yes	Destination address or zone:address (or - for any)
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
USER	no	User/group match
SWITCH	no	Runtime switch name
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Assign the FTP conntrack helper to inbound FTP traffic:
.RS
.nf
#ACTION  SOURCE  DEST            PROTO  DPORT
ftp      net     fw              tcp    21
.fi
.RE
.PP
Assign the SIP helper for VoIP:
.RS
.nf
sip      loc     net             udp    5060
.fi
.RE
.PP
Conntrack helper for TFTP:
.RS
.nf
tftp     loc     198.51.100.0/24 udp    69
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE and DEST columns accept
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-notrack (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

